  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed combinations; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development and is described narratively in the supporting technical report, confirming that inlet flow rate and impeller rotational speed are the primary drivers of hemolysis index variance. All 13 credibility factors are assessed and achieved levels meet or exceed required levels. Decision: Accepted.",
